wikipedia_page.main: William Frederick Dunnill (1880–1936) was an English cathedral organist, who served in St. Philip's Cathedral, Birmingham.

response: The cathedral has had six organists since 1888, of which Jonathan Bielby, MBE was the longest serving organist in an English cathedral. Previous organists have included composer Newell Smith Wallbank. Assistant organists have included William Frederick Dunnill and John Scott.
|1904–1914 || William Frederick Dunnill FRCO ARCM || (1880–1936) formerly organist of Christ Church, Surbiton and St Luke's Church, Bromley, latterly organist of Birmingham Cathedral
